  "body": "Something I ran into while working on #2869. Here's what happens:\r\n\r\nAssuming you're part of a bunch of chats, doesn't matter if public channels or one on one chats, if there are mentions in any of the chats, the message count badge is correctly shown for individual items. However, when activating any of the chats, the badge count persists, while it should actually go away (as mentions could then be considered as \"read\").\r\n\r\nThey only disappear after the user switches to a different view (e.g. a community or settings).\r\n\r\nIt seems we're not signalling correctly the clearance of the counter.",
